<BR><DIV CLASS="c4"><P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">Aug. 10--Greeley surgeon helps children in central America</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">Dr. Daniel Hatch, a foot and ankle surgeon in Greeley, has just returned from his semi annual medical mission trip to the Yucatan Crippled Children's Project.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">He has donated his time over the past nine years taking surgical residents from North Colorado Medical Center. He treated children with congenital foot and ankle deformities in the Yucatan towns of Merida and Progresso, so they can walk and wear shoes. Two days are spent in surgery, and the last day is in a clinic where more than 90 children were screened for future trips. Hatch has practiced in Greeley for 30 years and is past president of the American College of Foot and Ankle Surgeons. He can be reached at (970) 351-0900.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">A&amp;P breaks ground on Grace Pointe expansion </SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">Adolfson &amp; Peterson Construction on Aug. 1 joined with the Grace Pointe Continuing Care Community, Lantz-Boggio Architects and Continuum Health to kick off the expansion of the Grace Pointe Continuing Care Senior Campus in Greeley. Grace Pointe provides independent living and assisted living, nursing, rehabilitation and memory care services.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">The Grace Pointe Project Phase I was completed five years ago; today we are very excited to break ground on Phase II,&quot; commented Jason Heustis, Senior Project Manager for A&amp;P. The HUD project includes three expansions to the fully occupied facility. The first expansion, being the largest, consists of 26 apartments, while the other expansions are to the dining room in the rehabilitation wing and to the dining room in the assisted living wing.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">A&amp;P anticipates the 28,000-square-foot project to be completed by March 2015.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">Local company earns Patriot Award</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">Connecting Point's president Ted Warner, and vice president of sales, Scott Warner, have been given the Patriot Award for their support of employees who also are members of the Air and Army National Guard.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">Two employees, John Cox and Michael Brown, will be deploying over the next few weeks and can look forward to keeping their jobs up on their return. Cox, assigned as an aircraft crew chief to the 153rd Airlift Wing, Wyoming Air National Guard, will be away for four months supporting combat airlift operations including airdrops, medical evacuation, troop movements in support of Operation Enduring Freedom from an undisclosed Middle Eastern location.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">Brown, assigned to the 1158th Army Space Support Company, Colorado Army National Guard, will be deploying with the 193rd Military Police Battalion for 14 months. He will be stationed at the naval base in Guantanamo Bay Cuba.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">The Patriot Award reflects the efforts made to support citizen warriors through a wide-range of measures including flexible schedules, time off prior to and after deployment, caring for families and granting leaves of absence if needed, according to the Employer Support of the Guard and Reserve, a Department of Defense office established in 1972 to promote cooperation and understanding between Reserve Component Service members and their civilian employers. Connecting Point, 2401 17th St., has operated locally in Greeley for more than 30 years.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">True Abundance is now a 3-generation business</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">True Abundance Property Management can now brag it has a third generation helping run the business.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">True Abundance has been in business for eight years and has always been a family run business, run by Tony and Diane Quigley. Their daughter, Michele Gerbitz, has been working for them for seven years as head of maintenance. The Quigley's granddaughter, Alexandra Quigley, has joined the business as a showing agent while she attends Aims Community College.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">True Abundance Property Management is a full service Property Management Company and we also do Leasing for Weld County and Loveland. Call (970) 352-5732.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">Financial adviser attends national conference</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">Larry Hubbard, a financial adviser with Ameriprise Financial, qualified for and attended the 2014 National Conference, which was held in Boston.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">To earn this achievement, Hubbard established himself as one of the company's top advisers achieving high levels in production, client service and client satisfaction, according to a news release.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">Hubbard's office is located at 1711 61st Ave., Suite 200, Greeley.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">For more information, go to ameriprise.com or www.ameripriseadvisors.com/larry.hubbard.</SPAN></P>
